IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
   PROGRAM-ID.   RECALL-DOCS.
   AUTHOR.       SEMANTICINTENT.
   DATE-WRITTEN. 2026-04-06.
   PAGE-TITLE.   "RECALL Documentation".
   DESCRIPTION.  "The complete RECALL language reference — divisions, types, elements, diagnostics, and CLI.".
   FAVICON.      "/favicon.ico".

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
   COPY FROM "theme.rcpy".

DATA DIVISION.
   WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.

      * ── Section bodies ────────────────────────────────────
      01 INTRO-BODY      PIC X(240) VALUE "RECALL is a declarative web interface language with COBOL-inspired syntax. It compiles `.rcl` source files to self-contained, zero-dependency HTML. Every page embeds its source in an HTML comment — view source, see origin.".
      01 DIVISIONS-BODY  PIC X(200) VALUE "Every RECALL program has exactly five divisions, declared in order. Borrowed directly from COBOL — explicit, readable, non-negotiable. COMPONENT DIVISION is optional; all others are required.".
      01 PIC-BODY        PIC X(220) VALUE "Every DATA DIVISION field carries a PIC type. The compiler validates every DISPLAY statement against the element's type contract — wrong type, wrong format, no output. Run `recall schema` to query the live registry.".
      01 ELEMENTS-BODY   PIC X(160) VALUE "RECALL provides 20 built-in elements invoked with DISPLAY. Run `recall schema` to query the live element registry from the installed compiler.".
      01 COPY-BODY       PIC X(240) VALUE "Copybooks use the `.rcpy` extension — a reference to COBOL's `.cpy` format. They are never compiled standalone; only COPY FROM'd into `.rcl` programs at compile time. `recall build` skips `.rcpy` files automatically.".
      01 COMPONENTS-BODY PIC X(210) VALUE "Components are reusable layout fragments defined in COMPONENT DIVISION. Each declares an ACCEPTS list — the DATA DIVISION field names it expects. Callers bind fields with WITH DATA at invocation.".
      01 VALUE-LANG-BODY PIC X(240) VALUE "Three features modernise the data layer. VALUE BLOCK supports multi-line string literals. RECORD types define reusable group shapes declared once and expanded anywhere. COMMENT clauses attach intent metadata for AI tooling.".
      01 LOAD-BODY       PIC X(240) VALUE "LOAD FROM reads a JSON or CSV file at compile time and injects its contents into the DATA DIVISION. Scalars become WORKING-STORAGE fields. Arrays become ITEMS groups. No runtime — values are baked into the compiled HTML.".
      01 DIAG-BODY       PIC X(240) VALUE "RECALL enforces 26 structured diagnostic codes. Each code is stable, searchable, and documentable. If a program compiles, it is valid. If not, the compiler tells you exactly what is wrong, where, and how to fix it.".
      01 STRICT-BODY     PIC X(250) VALUE "Strict mode promotes all warnings to errors — zero tolerance for CI pipelines. Machine-readable JSON output includes source lines and caret strings so editor integrations and AI tools can render diagnostics without parsing ANSI sequences.".
      01 CLI-BODY        PIC X(220) VALUE "The RECALL CLI provides commands for compilation, validation, auto-fix, history diffing, and introspection. All commands accept `.rcl` files. Copybooks (`.rcpy`) are resolved automatically during compilation.".
      01 LIB-BODY        PIC X(210) VALUE "@semanticintent/recall-ui is the standard component library. Install once and COPY FROM its `.rcpy` files — the dark theme, nav, hero, stat-section, card-section, and footer are ready to use.".

      * ── Code examples ─────────────────────────────────────
      01 INSTALL-CMD     PIC X(60)  VALUE "npm install -g @semanticintent/recall-compiler".

      01 MINIMAL-EX      PIC X(340) VALUE "IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
   PROGRAM-ID.   MY-SITE.
   PAGE-TITLE.   Hello World.
   AUTHOR.       Your Name.
   DATE-WRITTEN. 2026-04-06.

DATA DIVISION.
   WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
      01 HERO-HEAD PIC X(20) VALUE Hello World.

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
   RENDER.
      DISPLAY HEADING-1 HERO-HEAD.
   STOP RUN.".

      01 PIC-EX          PIC X(320) VALUE "DATA DIVISION.
   WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
      01 PAGE-TITLE  PIC X(60)  VALUE My Site.
      01 VISIT-COUNT PIC 9(6)   VALUE 142398.
      01 PUBLISHED   PIC DATE   VALUE 2026-04-06.
      01 LOGO-SRC    PIC URL    VALUE https://example.com/logo.svg.
      01 ACCURACY    PIC PCT    VALUE 94.".

      01 COMPONENT-DEF-EX PIC X(360) VALUE "COMPONENT DIVISION.
   DEFINE PAGE-HERO.
      ACCEPTS HERO-TITLE REQUIRED, HERO-SUBTITLE, CTA-LABEL.
      DISPLAY SECTION WITH LAYOUT STACK WITH PADDING LARGE.
         DISPLAY HEADING-1 HERO-TITLE.
         DISPLAY PARAGRAPH HERO-SUBTITLE.
         DISPLAY BUTTON CTA-LABEL WITH STYLE PRIMARY.
      STOP SECTION.
   END DEFINE.".

      01 COMPONENT-USE-EX PIC X(440) VALUE "DATA DIVISION.
   WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
      01 SITE-TITLE PIC X(60) VALUE Launch Day.
      01 SITE-BODY  PIC X(200) VALUE Ready when you are.
      01 BTN-LABEL  PIC X(20) VALUE Get Started.

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
   RENDER.
      DISPLAY PAGE-HERO WITH DATA HERO-TITLE, HERO-SUBTITLE, CTA-LABEL
         WITH HERO-TITLE SITE-TITLE
         WITH HERO-SUBTITLE SITE-BODY
         WITH CTA-LABEL BTN-LABEL.
   STOP RUN.".

      01 REQUIRED-EX     PIC X(200) VALUE "ACCEPTS PAGE-TITLE REQUIRED, SUBTITLE, BADGE.
* RCL-017 fires when PAGE-TITLE is not provided at the call site.
* SUBTITLE and BADGE are optional — no error if omitted.".

      01 COMMENT-EX      PIC X(200) VALUE "01 FETCH-SCORE PIC X(10) VALUE 2978
   COMMENT CAL fetch score — higher is better.

01 REVIEW-DATE PIC DATE VALUE 2027-09-30
   COMMENT Scheduled review window for prognostic case.".

      01 VALUE-BLOCK-EX  PIC X(140) VALUE "01 BODY-TEXT PIC X VALUE BLOCK.   First paragraph of content here.   Second paragraph continues here. END VALUE.".

      01 RECORD-EX       PIC X(200) VALUE "RECORD CARD-SHAPE WITH FIELDS   CARD-TITLE  PIC X(60)   CARD-BODY   PIC X(200).   01 CARDS RECORD CARD-SHAPE ROWS 4.".

      01 LOAD-JSON-EX    PIC X(240) VALUE "DATA DIVISION.\n   LOAD FROM brief.json.\n\n* brief.json keys map to field names:\n{\n  HERO-TITLE: Streaming Consolidation,\n  STATS: [ { VALUE: 2451, LABEL: FETCH Score } ]\n}".
      01 LOAD-CSV-EX     PIC X(260) VALUE "DATA DIVISION.\n   LOAD FROM metrics.csv.\n\n* header row becomes column names:\nNAME,SCORE,LAYER\nRevenue (D3),75,origin\nQuality (D5),62,momentum\n\n* Auto-generates METRICS group.".

      01 COMPILE-EX      PIC X(80)  VALUE "recall compile my-site.rcl
recall compile my-site.rcl --out dist/".

      01 BUILD-EX        PIC X(60)  VALUE "recall build src/ --out public/
recall build src/".

      01 CHECK-EX        PIC X(200) VALUE "recall check my-site.rcl
recall check my-site.rcl --strict
recall check my-site.rcl --format json
recall check my-site.rcl --quiet
recall check my-site.rcl --inspect".

      01 FIX-EX          PIC X(220) VALUE "recall fix my-site.rcl --dry-run   * show what would change
recall fix my-site.rcl --yes       * apply all fixes without prompt
recall fix my-site.rcl             * interactive — confirm each fix".

      01 HISTORY-EX      PIC X(80)  VALUE "recall history my-site.rcl
recall history my-site.rcl --commits 5".

      01 STATS-EX        PIC X(40)  VALUE "recall stats my-site.rcl".

      01 SCHEMA-EX       PIC X(120) VALUE "recall schema             * list all elements and PIC types
recall schema --json       * machine-readable output".

      01 EXPLAIN-EX      PIC X(60)  VALUE "recall explain RCL-001
recall explain RCL-W05".

      01 EXIT-CODES-EX   PIC X(140) VALUE "0 — clean, no errors or warnings
1 — errors present, no output written
2 — warnings present, compiled unless --strict".

      01 DIAGNOSTIC-EX   PIC X(250) VALUE "ERROR [RCL-001] type-mismatch — my-site.rcl:14:8
  DISPLAY HEADING-1 HERO-STAT
                    ^^^^^^^^^
  Type mismatch
  HEADING-1 expects PIC X — HERO-STAT is PIC 9(4)
  Hint: use DISPLAY LABEL HERO-STAT for numeric display".

      01 JSON-EX         PIC X(320) VALUE "recall check my-site.rcl --format json

{
  errors: 1, warnings: 0,
  diagnostics: [{
    code: RCL-001, severity: error,
    category: type-mismatch,
    line: 14, col: 8,
    message: Type mismatch,
    source: DISPLAY HEADING-1 HERO-STAT,
    caret:                     ^^^^^^^^^
  }]
}".

      01 LIB-INSTALL-EX  PIC X(50)  VALUE "npm install @semanticintent/recall-ui".

      01 LIB-USAGE-EX    PIC X(700) VALUE "ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
   COPY FROM @semanticintent/recall-ui/themes/dark.rcpy.

COMPONENT DIVISION.
   COPY FROM @semanticintent/recall-ui/components/nav.rcpy.
   COPY FROM @semanticintent/recall-ui/components/hero.rcpy.
   COPY FROM @semanticintent/recall-ui/components/stat-section.rcpy.
   COPY FROM @semanticintent/recall-ui/components/footer.rcpy.

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
   RENDER.
      DISPLAY SITE-NAV     WITH DATA SITE-LOGO, NAV-ITEMS.
      DISPLAY PAGE-HERO    WITH DATA HERO-TITLE, HERO-SUBTITLE, CTA-LABEL, CTA-HREF.
      DISPLAY STAT-SECTION WITH DATA SECTION-TITLE, STATS, STAT-COLUMNS.
      DISPLAY SITE-FOOTER  WITH DATA FOOTER-TEXT.
   STOP RUN.".

   ITEMS SECTION.

      * ── Division reference table ──────────────────────────
      01 DIVISION-REF.
         05 ROW-1.
            10 COL-DIV  PIC X(30)  VALUE "IDENTIFICATION DIVISION".
            10 COL-REQ  PIC X(10)  VALUE "REQUIRED".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Program metadata — PROGRAM-ID, PAGE-TITLE, AUTHOR, DATE-WRITTEN, DESCRIPTION, FAVICON.".
         05 ROW-2.
            10 COL-DIV  PIC X(30)  VALUE "ENVIRONMENT DIVISION".
            10 COL-REQ  PIC X(10)  VALUE "REQUIRED".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(110) VALUE "Theme and config — VIEWPORT, COLOR-MODE, PALETTE, FONT, STYLE-BLOCK. Supports COPY FROM for theme inheritance.".
         05 ROW-3.
            10 COL-DIV  PIC X(30)  VALUE "DATA DIVISION".
            10 COL-REQ  PIC X(10)  VALUE "REQUIRED".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(115) VALUE "Fields and groups — WORKING-STORAGE for scalars, ITEMS for groups. LOAD FROM ingests JSON or CSV at compile time.".
         05 ROW-4.
            10 COL-DIV  PIC X(30)  VALUE "COMPONENT DIVISION".
            10 COL-REQ  PIC X(10)  VALUE "OPTIONAL".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(130) VALUE "Component definitions — DEFINE, ACCEPTS, END DEFINE. COPY FROM imports .rcpy libraries. WITH DATA binds fields at invocation.".
         05 ROW-5.
            10 COL-DIV  PIC X(30)  VALUE "PROCEDURE DIVISION".
            10 COL-REQ  PIC X(10)  VALUE "REQUIRED".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Render logic — named sections with DISPLAY statements. Must end with STOP RUN.".

      * ── PIC type reference table ───────────────────────────
      01 PIC-TYPE-REF.
         05 TYPE-1.
            10 COL-TYPE  PIC X(15) VALUE "PIC X(n)".
            10 COL-KIND  PIC X(20) VALUE "string".
            10 COL-USAGE PIC X(90) VALUE "Text up to n characters. Used by HEADING-1, PARAGRAPH, LABEL, BUTTON, and most elements.".
         05 TYPE-2.
            10 COL-TYPE  PIC X(15) VALUE "PIC X".
            10 COL-KIND  PIC X(20) VALUE "string".
            10 COL-USAGE PIC X(95) VALUE "Single character. Shorthand for PIC X(1). Also used with VALUE BLOCK for auto-sized strings.".
         05 TYPE-3.
            10 COL-TYPE  PIC X(15) VALUE "PIC 9(n)".
            10 COL-KIND  PIC X(20) VALUE "numeric".
            10 COL-USAGE PIC X(100) VALUE "Integer up to n digits. Use LABEL or STAT-GRID for display. Non-numeric VALUE triggers RCL-012.".
         05 TYPE-4.
            10 COL-TYPE  PIC X(15) VALUE "PIC 9".
            10 COL-KIND  PIC X(20) VALUE "boolean-numeric".
            10 COL-USAGE PIC X(80) VALUE "0 or 1. Boolean flag. Single-digit numeric.".
         05 TYPE-5.
            10 COL-TYPE  PIC X(15) VALUE "PIC DATE".
            10 COL-KIND  PIC X(20) VALUE "date".
            10 COL-USAGE PIC X(80) VALUE "ISO 8601 date string (YYYY-MM-DD). Malformed values trigger RCL-009.".
         05 TYPE-6.
            10 COL-TYPE  PIC X(15) VALUE "PIC URL".
            10 COL-KIND  PIC X(20) VALUE "url".
            10 COL-USAGE PIC X(80) VALUE "Must begin with http, https, or /. Malformed values trigger RCL-010.".
         05 TYPE-7.
            10 COL-TYPE  PIC X(15) VALUE "PIC PCT".
            10 COL-KIND  PIC X(20) VALUE "percent".
            10 COL-USAGE PIC X(80) VALUE "Integer 0-100. Out-of-range values trigger RCL-011.".
         05 TYPE-8.
            10 COL-TYPE  PIC X(15) VALUE "GROUP".
            10 COL-KIND  PIC X(20) VALUE "group".
            10 COL-USAGE PIC X(112) VALUE "Named group declared in ITEMS SECTION. Referenced by USING clause in TABLE, STAT-GRID, CARD-LIST, NAVIGATION.".

      * ── Element reference table ────────────────────────────
      01 ELEMENT-REF.
         05 ROW-1.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "HEADING-1/2/3".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "value WITH STYLE MONO/SANS".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Heading at level 1, 2 or 3. Expects PIC X.".
         05 ROW-2.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "PARAGRAPH".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "value WITH COLOR MUTED/TEXT/ACCENT".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Body paragraph. Expects PIC X. Accepts `citations YES` for inline footnote links.".
         05 ROW-3.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "LABEL".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "value".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Uppercase eyebrow label. Use before headings to add section context. Accepts PIC X or PIC 9.".
         05 ROW-4.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "CODE-BLOCK".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "value WITH LANGUAGE bash/cobol/json".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Monospace code block with optional language hint for syntax display.".
         05 ROW-5.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "BUTTON".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "value ON-CLICK GOTO href".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Link styled as a button. WITH STYLE PRIMARY, GHOST, or OUTLINE.".
         05 ROW-6.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "LINK".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "value WITH HREF url".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Inline anchor. WITH TARGET BLANK opens in a new tab.".
         05 ROW-7.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "IMAGE".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "WITH SRC url WITH ALT text".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Image element. WITH SIZE FULL or HALF sets display width. SRC must be PIC URL.".
         05 ROW-8.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "DIVIDER".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "WITH STYLE DASHED".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Horizontal rule. WITH SPACING SMALL or LARGE controls vertical margin.".
         05 ROW-9.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "BANNER".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "value".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Full-width accent-coloured banner bar.".
         05 ROW-10.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "CALLOUT".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "value WITH TYPE NOTE/TIP/WARNING/DANGER".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Highlighted callout block with typed accent colour. Expects PIC X.".
         05 ROW-11.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "INPUT".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "value WITH TYPE text/email/search".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Text input field. The value sets the placeholder label.".
         05 ROW-12.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "CARD-LIST".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "USING group WITH COLUMNS 2/3".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Card grid from an ITEMS group. WITH HOVER-LIFT YES adds card lift on hover.".
         05 ROW-13.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "TABLE".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "USING group WITH COLUMNS col1, col2".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(105) VALUE "Data table from an ITEMS group. COLUMNS sets header labels; cells map to level-10 fields by position.".
         05 ROW-14.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "STAT-GRID".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "USING group WITH COLUMNS 3/4/6".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Metric display grid. Detects -VALUE and -LABEL field pairs per row automatically.".
         05 ROW-15.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "TIMELINE".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "USING group".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Chronological timeline rendered from an ITEMS group.".
         05 ROW-16.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "TABS".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "USING group".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Interactive tabbed panels. Each item in the group becomes one tab with a label and content.".
         05 ROW-17.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "NAVIGATION".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "USING group WITH LOGO text".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Top navigation bar with logo and links. WITH STICKY YES fixes it while scrolling.".
         05 ROW-18.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "SIDEBAR-NAV".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "USING group WITH LOGO text".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Sidebar navigation panel. Only valid inside LAYOUT SIDEBAR. WITH STICKY YES keeps it fixed.".
         05 ROW-19.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "FOOTER".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "WITH TEXT value WITH ALIGN CENTER".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(100) VALUE "Page footer with centred or left-aligned text.".
         05 ROW-20.
            10 COL-NAME PIC X(20)  VALUE "SECTION".
            10 COL-ARGS PIC X(40)  VALUE "ID id WITH LAYOUT type WITH PADDING size".
            10 COL-DESC PIC X(110) VALUE "Layout container. LAYOUT: CENTERED, STACK, GRID, SIDEBAR, SPLIT. Supports nesting. Closed with STOP SECTION.".

